Taiwan Stocks Movers: Chimei Innolux, TPK Holding Co.

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-08-05T05:48:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-05/taiwan-stocks-movers-chimei-innolux-tpk-holding-co-.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 1:30 p.m. close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index fell 464.14 points, or 5.6 percent, to
7,853.13, the fourth day of declines and the biggest slump since
Nov. 6, 2008. The benchmark index entered a so-called
correction, falling 13 percent from its June 1 high. The index
fell 9.2 percent this week, the worst weekly loss since October
2008.  Chimei Innolux Corp. (3481)  (3481 TT) tumbled 7 percent to NT$14,
a record low. The country’s largest liquid-crystal display maker
reported a net loss of NT$13 billion ($449 million) in the three
months ended June 30, compared with a NT$9.5 billion profit a
year earlier, the Miaoli, Taiwan-based company said yesterday.
The average of 13 analysts’ estimates compiled by Bloomberg was
for a loss of NT$6.47 billion.  TPK Holding Co. (3673 TT) slid 6.9 percent to NT$677, the
lowest closing level since Feb. 11. The touch panel maker’s
earnings-per-share may fall up to 34 percent in 2013 if Apple
Inc.’s iPhones and iPads adopt new “integrated touch”
technology, said HSBC Holdings Plc analyst Jerry Tai in a note
yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
